		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Mar 31st 2:07 PM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98606563093501&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=2&mid=98606563093501&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=98606563093501"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98606563093501></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=43157"><span id=>Malachi</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>4 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Easy one. First, you can Backstab while autoattack is on, don't make that button, just make a backstab button. For the other, like I have, do this:<br>put pickpocket in any hotkey slot. The slots are numbered like this<br>1 2<br>3 4<br>5 6<br>Now, go to socials. Click the right arrow and you'll get a *mostly* blank or all blank row of keys. Click on one.<br>For the name, I call mine Kill. Don't know why, I just did.<br>With one command per line, make it look like this:<br>/attack<br>/do 6 (where 6 is the pp hotkey number)<br>/attack<br><br>Then click done.<br>The button will appear under your socials. Left click it and hold down the mouse button. The button will stick to your cursor. Move your cursor to an empty hotkey slot (has to be in the same set of 6 as the pp hotkey) and click the mouse, it will stick.<br><br>Now when in battle, run up to the mob and backstab him. Immediatly press A. Now that autoattack is on, press your new homemade hotkey. The first /attack turns auto OFF so it can then pickpocket and then the second /attack turns it back on. Ta Da!<br><br>Don't forget to keep backstabbing as soon as it's an option, and press your new hotkey every time pp becomes available!<br><br>You MUST turn on auto attack before using the button, because if you don't it will turn it on, try to do a pp and fail cuz attack is on, then turn attack back off.<br><br>I leveled my pp from about 40-92 this way in about 5 hours.<br><br>That's my two cents. Where's my change?<br>~Malachi<br>19th Level Rogue. Me kill badguys.<br>*snicker* Sometimes good guys too....</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
